name: Country that cares for me
description:
I live on Dharug country, bordering with the land of the Gundungurra peoples. My indigenous ancestors come from off the mainland. But this place, with its mists of blue, the place I live and was born, where my mother and father live, where my grandfather once lived, it is my home and my country. It is the country I belong to. The country that takes care of me.

This artwork is an animated photograph of handmade wool felt, made using wet felting methods. Rose Jackson, 2021
